<TITLE>Jozef Karol Hell</TITLE>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF MENTION="1" SYNFUNC="subj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="plain" REG08-TYPE="name" ENTITY="0">Jozef Karol Hell</REFEX></REF>
 (Slovak), Hell József Károly (Hungarian), Josef/ph Karl Hell (German) (1713-1789) was a mining engineer and inventor 
<REF MENTION="2" SYNFUNC="subj_rel-clause" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="nominative" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" ENTITY="0">who</REFEX></REF>
, in 1755, invented the water-pillar, the world's first water pump machine. It is mainly used today for oil extraction. 
<REF MENTION="3" SYNFUNC="subj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="nominative" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" ENTITY="0">he</REFEX></REF>
 also proposed construction of the tajchy reservoirs around Banská Štiavnica. 
<REF MENTION="4" SYNFUNC="subj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="0"><REFEX CASE="nominative" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" ENTITY="0">he</REFEX></REF>
 was a son of 
<REF MENTION="1" SYNFUNC="obj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="1"><REFEX CASE="plain" REG08-TYPE="name" ENTITY="1">Maximilian Hell</REFEX></REF>
 and a student of 
<REF MENTION="1" SYNFUNC="obj" SYNCAT="np" SEMCAT="person" ENTITY="2"><REFEX CASE="plain" REG08-TYPE="name" ENTITY="2">Samuel Mikoviny</REFEX></REF>
.
</PARAGRAPH>
